	"description": "What is the Dunning-Kruger Effect?\nHey there, fellow developers! Imagine this. You&#x27;ve just landed your first tech\njob or maybe you&#x27;re fresh out of a coding boot camp/university. You&#x27;re pumped,\nexcited, and ready to show the world with everything you&#x27;ve got. \n\nBut wait a minute—ever heard of the Dunning-Kruger Effect?\n\nNo, it&#x27;s not the name of a cool Unicorn company or a secret programming\nlanguage. It&#x27;s actually a psychological phenomenon where people think they know\nmore than they actually do. ",
